      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou1-cpb-hemolysis-claim",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model adequately predicts worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for Class II CPB device",
      "description": "The CFD model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump, when applied under the COU1 operating envelope (flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM), produces hemolysis predictions of sufficient fidelity to support regulatory decision-making regarding worst-case operating conditions. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion is met across all evaluated configurations, supporting the conclusion that the predicate device comparison is conservative. This claim encompasses model form adequacy for turbulence-driven shear stress prediction, numerical accuracy of the hemolysis power-law integration, and representativeness of the validation dataset to the clinical COU.",
      "scope": "Class II CPB device, Model Risk Level 2, five operating points as specified in COU1",
      "purpose": "Support 510(k) submission decision regarding worst-case hemolysis operating conditions"
    }
  ],
